docs {
  # List Pareto Hardware Configurations

  Returns hardware configurations used in Pareto chart visualizations.

  ## Data Shape

  ```json
  [
    {
      "id": "gb200x72-dynamo-fp4",
      "label": "GB200x72 w/ Dynamo TRT FP4",
      "hardwareConfig": "GB200x72_Dynamo_TRT_FP4",
      "vendorId": "nvidia",
      "color": "#2563eb",
      "maxThroughput": 700000,
      "minConcurrency": 1,
      "maxConcurrency": 4096
    }
  ]
  ```

  ## Fields

  | Field | Type | Description |
  |-------|------|-------------|
  | id | string | Unique configuration identifier |
  | label | string | Human-readable display label |
  | hardwareConfig | string | Technical configuration name |
  | vendorId | string | Reference to vendor |
  | color | string | Hex color for chart rendering |
  | maxThroughput | number | Maximum achievable throughput (tok/s) |
  | minConcurrency | number | Minimum concurrent clients |
  | maxConcurrency | number | Maximum concurrent clients |

  ## Available Configurations

  - `gb200x72-dynamo-fp4`: NVIDIA GB200 with Dynamo TRT FP4
  - `h200x8-vllm-fp8`: NVIDIA H200 with vLLM FP8
  - `mi300x-rocm-fp8`: AMD MI300X with ROCm FP8
  - `gaudi3-synapse-bf16`: Intel Gaudi3 with Synapse BF16

  ## Filter Examples

  - `?vendorId=nvidia` - NVIDIA configurations only
  - `?vendorId=amd` - AMD configurations only
}
